shed_date                = \n| population_footnotes            = <!-- for references: use <ref> tags -->\n| population_total                = 1630\n| population_as_of                = 2005\n| population_demonym              = \n| population_note                 = \n| population_density_km2          = auto\n| timezone                        = [[Central European Time|CET]]\n| utc_offset                      = +1\n| timezone_DST                    = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n| utc_offset_DST                  = +2\n| postal_code_type                = [[List of postal codes in the Netherlands|Postal code]]\n| postal_code                     = \n| area_code_type                  = [[Telephone numbers in the Netherlands|Dialing code]]\n| area_code                       = Omphemetse\n| website                         = \n| footnotes                       = \n| official_name                   = \n| translit_lang1_info             = \n| translit_lang1                  = \n}}\n'''Ophemert''' is a village in the [[Netherlands|Dutch]] province of [[Gelderland]]. It is a part of the municipality of [[Neerijnen]], and lies about 5&nbsp;km south of [[Tiel]].\n\nOphemert was a separate municipality between 1818 and 1978, when it was merged with [[Neerijnen]].<ref>Ad van der Meer and Onno Boonstra, \"Repertorium van Nederlandse gemeenten\", KNAW, 2006. [http://www.knaw.nl/cfdata/publicaties/detail.cfm?boeken__ordernr=20061061]</ref>\n\nIn 2001, the village of Ophemert had 1020 inhabitants. The built-up area of the village was 0.30&nbsp;km\u00b2, and contained 389 residences.<ref name=\"CBS\">Statistics Netherlands (CBS), [http://www.cbs.nl/nl-NL/menu/themas/milieu-natuur-ruimte/ruimte/publicaties/cartografie-geografie/geografische-data/2001-bevolkingskernen-in-nederland.htm ''Bevolkingskernen in Nederland 2001'']. (Statistics are for the continuous built-up area).</ref>\nThe statistical area \"Ophemert\", which also can include the peripheral parts of the village, as well as the surrounding countryside, has a population of around 1670.<ref name=\"CBS2\">Statistics Netherlands (CBS), [http://statline.cbs.nl/ ''Statline: Kerncijfers wijken en buurten 2003-2005'']. As of 1 January 2005.</refle \n\nBy:Omphemetse Mokhutsane\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.atlas1868.nl/ge/ophemert.html Map of the former municipality in 1868]\n\n[[Category:Populated places in Gelderland]]\n[[Category:Former municipalities of Gelderland]]\n[[Category:Neerijnen]]\n\n\n{{Gelderland-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Ophemert\n| settlement_type         = Village\n| other_name              = <!-- if different from name -->\n| native_name             = <!-- if different from name -->\n| native_name_lang        = nl\n| image_skyline           = Kasteel ophemert.JPG\n| image_alt               =\n| image_caption           = Ophemert Castle\n| image_flag              =\n| image_shield            = Ophemert wapen.svg\n| nickname                =\n| motto                   =\n| image_map               = LocatieNeerijnen.png\n| map_caption             =\n| image_map1              = Map NL - Neerijnen - Ophemert.png\n| map_caption1            = The village centre (red) and the statistical district (light green) of Ophemert in the municipality of Neerijnen.\n| pushpin_map             = <!-- Netherlands -->\n| pushpin_label_position  =\n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location in the Netherlands\n| subdivision_type        = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n| subdivision_name        = [[Netherlands]]\n| subdivision_type1       = [[Provinces of the Netherlands|Province]]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Gelderland]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[List of municipalities of the Netherlands|Municipality]]\n| subdivision_name2       = [[Neerijnen]]\n| leader_title            =\n| leader_name             =\n| leader_party            =\n| coordinates             = {{coord|51|50|43|N|5|23|3|E|region:NL