": "{{short description|2020 single by Little Mix}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name          = Break Up Song\n| cover         = Little Mix - Break Up Song.png\n| alt           =\n| type          = single\n| artist        = [[Little Mix]]\n| released      = {{start date|2020|03|27|df=y}}\n| recorded      =\n| format        =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| studio        = \n| genre         = [[Synth-pop]]<ref name=\"List\"/>\n| length        = {{Duration|m=3|s=20}}\n| label         = [[RCA Records#Other RCA labels|RCA UK]]\n| writer        =\n* Jade Thirlwall\n* Perrie Edwards\n* Leigh-Anne Pinnock\n* [[Camille Purcell]]\n* Frank Nobel\n* Linus N\u00f6rdstrom\n| producer      =\n* [[Kamille]]\n* Goldfingers\n| prev_title    = [[One I've Been Missing]]\n| prev_year     = 2019\n| next_title    =\n| next_year     =\n| misc          ={{External music video|type=single|{{YouTube| Pa3C3blayWo |\"Break Up Song\"}}|header=Lyric video}}\n}}\n\"'''Break Up Song'''\" is a song by British girl group [[Little Mix]]. It was released by [[RCA Records|RCA UK]] on 27 March 2020 as the lead single from their upcoming sixth studio album.<ref name=\"Idolator\">{{cite web|url=https://www.idolator.com/7908442/let-their-new-era-begin-little-mix-announces-break-up-song|title=Let Their New Era Begin! Little Mix Announces \"Break Up Song\"|website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|last=Wass|first=Mike|date=24 March 2020|accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref> Group members Jade Thirlwall, Leigh-Anne Pinnock and Perrie Edwards wrote the song with Frank Nobel, and its producers [[Camille Purcell|Kamille]] and Goldfingers.<ref name=\"Clash\">{{cite web|url=https://www.clashmusic.com/news/little-mix-prep-new-single-break-up-song|title=Little Mix Prep New Single 'Break Up Song'|work=[[Clash (magazine)|Clash]]|last=Murray|first=Robin|date=24 March 2020|accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Qobuz\"/>\n\n==Background==\nLittle Mix members Perrie Edwards, Leigh-Anne Pinnock and Jade Thirlwall wrote \"Break Up Song\" with Frank Nobel, and its producers [[Camille Purcell|Kamille]] and Goldfingers.<ref name=\"Qobuz\">{{cite web|url=https://www.qobuz.com/gb-en/album/break-up-song-little-mix/bd5i2piwaosfb|title=Album Break Up Song, Little Mix|website=[[Qobuz]]|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> According to Thirlwall, they wrote the song more than a year prior to its release with [[1980s in music|1980s pop music]] and an element of nostalgia in mind, similar to that of their 2015 single \"[[Black Magic (Little Mix song)|Black Magic]]\".<ref name=\"Gay Times\">{{cite web|url=https://www.gaytimes.co.uk/culture/133775/little-mix-jade-on-how-this-new-era-is-all-about-having-fun/|title=Jade Thirlwall on how Little Mix's new era is all about having fun|last=Corner|first=Lewis|website=[[Gay Times]]|date=27 March 2020|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://revistaquem.globo.com/Musica/noticia/2020/03/little-mix-lanca-break-song-um-aperitivo.html|title=Little mix lan\u00e7a 'Break Up Song': 'Um aperitivo'|language=Portuguese|last=Bressani|first=Giulia|website=Revista Quem|date=27 March 2020|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref> Edwards, Pinnock and Thirlwall composed it during a whirl of creativity where they wrote seven songs with Kamille in one day, after having only one melody from a frustrating previous session.<ref name=\"BBC\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-52047394|title=Little Mix star Perrie Edwards talks new music, panic attacks and knitting|last=Savage|first=Mark|website=[[BBC News]]|date=27 March 2020|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Papelpop\">{{cite web|url=https://www.papelpop.com/2020/03/entrevista-perrie-edwards-fala-sobre-break-up-song-nova-fase-do-little-mix-e-lamenta-nao-ter-vindo-ao-brasil/|title=Entrevista: Perrie Edwards fala sobre 'Break Up Song', nova fase do Little Mix e lamenta n\u00e3o ter vindo ao Brasil|language=Portuguese|last=Sehn|first=Rafaela|website=Papelpop|date=27 March 2020|accessdate=29 March 2020}}</ref> The track's 1980s sound stemmed from a [[synthesiser]] they dabbled with in the studio.<ref name=\"Gay Times\"/>\n\nA different song was initially chosen as their sixth album's [[lead single]] with an accompanying music video already filmed. However, the group opted for \"Break Up Song\" at the last minute after hearing the [[Demo (music)|demo]] again during a playback session.<ref name=\"Gay Times\"/> The demo had only one verse and main line. Edwards described it as \"very basic at the time. The beat was all over the place and it was really, really rough - but it just had something about it.\"<ref name=\"BBC\"/> Thirlwall recalled, \"We got that jittery feeling that we had with '[[Shout Out to My Ex]]' and 'Black Magic' where it just felt special.\"<ref name=\"Gay Times\"/>\n\n==Composition==\nThirlwall described the track as \"a very feel-good kind of empowerment song about going out and just forgetting about all your woes and troubles\".<ref name=\"Idolator\"/> It was also called an \"80s-synth pop anthem\" about \"getting over the end of a relationship\".<ref name=\"List\">{{cite web|url=https://www.list.co.uk/article/115305-little-mix-to-drop-new-single-break-up-song-this-week/|title=Little Mix to drop new single Break Up Song this week|website=[[The List (magazine)|The List]]|date=24 March 2020|accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Promotion==\nA Little Mix-themed filter on [[Instagram]] was made available to the group's followers to promote the track.<ref name=\"Clash\"/> The song received a [[Spotify]] [[vertical video]] and a [[lyric video]], both released on 27 March 2020<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-Pc0BsjjUl/|title=Little Mix on Instagram: \"Break Up Song vertical video is up on @spotify \ud83d\udd25 Link in stories Thank you for all the love, we've missed you guys \ud83d\ude2d\"|via=[[Instagram]]|date=27 March 2020|accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Pa3C3blayWo|title=Little Mix - Break Up Song (Lyric Video)|via=[[YouTube]]|publisher=LittleMixVEVO|date=27 March 2020|accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref> as the latter was made by Kayleigh, a fan of the band from the Netherlands.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.capitalfm.com/artists/little-mix/break-up-song-lyric-video-fan-made/|title=Little Mix's 'Break Up Song' Lyric Video Was Made Entirely By A Fan|website=[[Capital (radio network)|Capital FM]]|date=27 March 2020 |type=Music Video|accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Personnel==\nCredits adapted from [[Qobuz]].<ref name=\"Qobuz\"/>\n\n*[[Camille Purcell|Kamille]]&nbsp;\u2013 production, keyboards, vocal production, bass, background vocals\n*Goldfingers&nbsp;\u2013 production, drums, keyboards, programming\n*Raphaella Mazaheri-Asadi&nbsp;\u2013 vocal production \n*Frank Nobel&nbsp;\u2013 drums, keyboards, programming\n*[[Phil Tan]]&nbsp;\u2013 mixing \n*Paul Norris&nbsp;\u2013 engineering\n*Bill Zimmerman&nbsp;\u2013 engineering assistance \n*Randy Merrill&nbsp;\u2013 mastering\n\n==Charts== \n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{single chart|Flanders Tip|24|artist=Little Mix|song=Break Up Song|rowheader=true|accessdate=3 April 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Canadian Hot Digital Song Sales (''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'')<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/little-mix/chart-history/CNS|title=Little Mix: Chart History - Hot Canadian Digital Song Sales|work=Billboard|accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref>\n| 49\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Euro Digital Songs]] (''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'')<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/Little-Mix/chart-history/euro-digital-song-sales|title=Little Mix Chart History (Euro Digital Song Sales)|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref>\n| 2\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Greece ([[IFPI Greece|IFPI]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ifpi.gr/digital_ien.html|title=Official IFPI Charts \u2013 Digital Singles Chart (International) \u2013 Week: 13/2020|publisher=[[IFPI Greece]]|access-date=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n| 81\n|-\n{{single chart|Hungarysingle|11|year=2020|week=14|artist=Little Mix|song=Break Up Song|rowheader=true|accessdate=10 April 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Ireland4|18|date=20200403|rowheader=true|accessdate=4 April 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Netherlands ([[Dutch Top 40|Dutch Top 40 Tipparade]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.top40.nl/tipparade/2020/week-14|title=Tipparade-lijst van week 14, 2020|language=Dutch|trans-title=Tip parade list from week 14, 2020|publisher=[[Dutch Top 40]]|accessdate=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n| 28\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Netherlands ([[MegaCharts|Single Tip]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://dutchcharts.nl/showitem.asp?interpret=Little+Mix&titel=Break+Up+Song&cat=s|title=Dutchcharts.nl \u2013 Little Mix \u2013 Break Up Song|work=[[MegaCharts]]|language=Dutch|accessdate=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n| 18\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| New Zealand Hot Singles ([[Recorded Music NZ|RMNZ]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nztop40.co.nz/chart/hotsingles?chart=4841|title=NZ Hot Singles Chart|publisher=[[Recorded Music NZ]]|date=6 April 2020|accessdate=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n| 9\n|-\n{{single chart|Portugal|142|artist=Little Mix|song=Break Up Song|rowheader=true|accessdate=9 April 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Scotland|2|date=20200403|rowheader=true|accessdate=4 April 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Switzerland|29|artist=Little Mix|song=Break Up Song|rowheader=true|accessdate=6 April 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|UK|9|date=20200403|rowheader=true|accessdate=4 April 2020}}\n|}\n\n==Release history==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Region\n! scope=\"col\"| Date\n! scope=\"col\"| Format\n! scope=\"col\"| Label(s)\n! scope=\"col\"| {{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Various\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 27 March 2020\n| {{hlist|[[Music download|Digita